{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Angola | country_link = Angola | continent = Africa | map_image = | map_caption = | map_size = | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +244 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = none | regulator = | plan_membership = | nsn_length = 9 | dial_plan_type = | number_format = | codes_list = }} [[Telephone]] numbers in [[Angola]] are 9 digits long (except for special 1xx service numbers like [[Police]] and [[Emergency]] services),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sccfd.org/travel.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-05-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080511201439/http://www.sccfd.org/travel.html |archivedate=2008-05-11 |df= }} Angola emergency numbers</ref> and must always be dialed in their entirety. Land-line (fixed-line) numbers start with [[Numerical digit|digit]] 2, followed by 1 or 2 [[Numerical digit|digits]] [[area code]] that corresponds to a [[geographic]] area.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.exxun.com/Angola/f_cm.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090628142203/http://www.exxun.com/Angola/f_cm.html |archivedate=2009-06-28 |df= }} Description of the Angola telephone network</ref> After the area code, there is the telecoms [[Network operator|operator]] identifier, which consists of 1 digit, then the subscriber number. [[Mobile phone|Mobile numbers]] have no [[geographic]] area, and they start with the operators identifier which currently are 91 and 92. (needs updating)
==Calling formats== * '''xxx xxx xxx''' Calls within Angola * '''+244 xxx xxx xxx''' Calls from outside Angola The NSN length is nine digits.
